wikipedia_page.main: George Caldwell (8 January 1807 – 5 March 1863) was an English cricketer who made his first-class cricket debut in 1829.

response: |Played in five first-class matches, four for MCC and one for an England side. Played in a number of other matches, mainly for Norfolk and Swaffam. Brother of George Caldwell.
* George Caldwell (politician) (1814–1866), U.S. Representative from Kentucky
